      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would prefer if you could move all this code under its own source file (e.g. android/ext4_resize.c or android/ext4_resize.cpp, and provide android/ext4_resize.h to declare the function(s) in here), the reason for this is that eventually, all this processing should happen in the top-level \u0027emulator\u0027 launcher process, to ensure that the same feature is supported by both the classic and the qemu2 codebases.\n\nI already plan to separate the partition management code from vl-android.c and hw/android/goldfish/nand.c to its own sources in the same way.\n\nAlso this means dropping qemu-specific dependencies, e.g. try to use android::base::System::get()-\u003efindBundledExecutable(\"resize2fs\"); to get the path to the executable. I know that for now, there are only Windows executable under bin/, and nothing under bin64/, but this can be solved by copying the 32-bit binaries into the bin64/ folder in android-rebuild.sh\n\nPing me if this isn\u0027t clear.",
      "parentUuid": "78f7fee1_a4478e20",
      "revId": "c33eb3b79e8e6f9ec28c2de735ffbd4becbf25c1",
