      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: should be size_in_MB, not \u0026size_in_MB.\n\nIn general, it\u0027s also typically better to avoid repeating hard-coded constants, i.e. use:\n\n  char array[ARRAY_SIZE];\n  snprintf(array, sizeof(array), ....);\n\ninstead of:\n\n  char array[ARRAY_SIZE];\n  snprintf(array, ARRAY_SIZE, ....);\n\nit avoids trivial but deadly errors when someone changes the size of the array but forgets other places where it is used.",
